It appears that there is no information available for the most recent five deputy prime ministers of Singapore. However, I can provide you with the universities attended by some of the deputy prime ministers of Singapore: 

Tharman Shanmugaratnam: attended the London School of Economics and Political Science.

Goh Chok Tong: studied at the University of Singapore (which later became the National University of Singapore). 

S. Jayakumar: graduated from the University of Singapore (National University of Singapore). 

Heng Swee Keat: holds a Bachelor of Arts in Economics degree from the University of Singapore (National University of Singapore). 

Lawrence Wong: earned his Bachelor of Science in Electrical and Electronics Engineering and a Master of Science in Electrical Engineering from the National University of Singapore. 

I could not find any information on their respective graduation years. Would you like me to search for more deputy prime ministers of Singapore and their alma maters?

functions.desc:
Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.
